# SEO — new or changed routes

Before editing or creating `app/**/page.tsx`, read in order:

1. `seo/README.md`
2. `seo/urls.md` — confirm or register the URL
3. `seo/globals.md`
4. `seo/pages/{page-type}.md` — create from `seo/pages/_template.md` if missing
5. `seo/indexing.md`
6. `seo/json-ld/` — schemas listed in the page spec
7. `seo/security-and-referrers.md` — if page has outbound links

## Requirements

- Use `buildPageMetadata()` / dedicated builders from `lib/seo/metadata.ts`
- Render JSON-LD via `<JsonLd data={...} />` from `components/seo/json-ld.tsx`
- Update `seo/urls.md` and `app/sitemap.ts` when adding indexable routes
- Do not hardcode titles, descriptions, or canonical URLs in page files

For UI work, also read `design-system/kerkida/pages/{page}.md` when it exists.
